com.google.template.soy.basetree

Interface NodeVisitor<N extends Node,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    N - A more specific subinterface of Node, or just Node if not applicable.
    R - The return type of this visitor.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractExprNodeVisitor, AbstractNodeVisitor, AbstractReturningExprNodeVisitor, AbstractReturningNodeVisitor, AbstractReturningSoyNodeVisitor, AbstractSoyNodeVisitor, AssertStrictAutoescapingVisitor, BuildAllDependeesMapVisitor, ChangeCallsToPassAllDataVisitor, CheckCallingParamTypesVisitor, CheckCallsVisitor, CheckDelegatesVisitor, CheckFunctionCallsVisitor, CheckTemplateParamsVisitor, CheckTemplateVisibility, ClearSoyDocStringsVisitor, CombineConsecutiveRawTextNodesVisitor, EvalVisitor, ExtractMsgsVisitor, FindCalleesNotInFileVisitor, FindIndirectParamsVisitor, FindTransitiveDepTemplatesVisitor, GenerateParseInfoVisitor, GenPyExprsVisitor, HasNodeTypesVisitor, InferRequiredSyntaxVersionVisitor, InsertMsgsVisitor, RemoveHtmlCommentsVisitor, RenameCssVisitor, RenderVisitor, ReplaceHasDataFunctionVisitor, ReportSyntaxVersionErrorsVisitor, ResolveExpressionTypesVisitor, ResolveNamesVisitor, ResolvePackageRelativeCssNamesVisitor, RewriteGenderMsgsVisitor, RewriteRemaindersVisitor, SetDefaultForDelcallAllowsEmptyDefaultVisitor, SetFullCalleeNamesVisitor, SimplifyVisitor, StrictDepsVisitor, TranslateToJsExprVisitor, VerifyPhnameAttrOnlyOnPlaceholdersVisitor

    public interface NodeVisitor<N extends Node,R>
    External interface for a node visitor. A visitor is basically a function implemented for some or all node classes, where the implementation can be different for each specific node class.

    Important: Do not use outside of Soy code (treat as superpackage-private).

      Executes the function defined by this visitor.
